ut addressing issues that he left to others. Doran?s idea of a core set of meanings for systematics ? or a ?unified field structure? ? is highly original, as is the integration of the systematic ideal and contemporary historical consciousness.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066769108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311049095440uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781442683297423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442683297.jpg  a978-3-11-049095-4  University of Toronto Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066769-1  UTP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG